{
  "stem": "22869.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the-- the religion that was imbued within me and that has nothing to do, I think, maybe with my parents or with the education that I had, it was-- it was purely that-- I consider myself lucky of picking it up again and continuing.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I can't see myself living a life without it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yet, I know that there are many friends who were my pals in school and in the Jewish school, who threw everything away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I've never in my life blamed them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I always tell my children that the ones who came back and are nonbelievers-- they are the normal ones.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The ones of us who do believe, they are the crazy ones.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because no normal human being, unless he's made out of iron or steel-- his will-- can go through all that stuff and come back and still-- believing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I really am appreciative to-- to whoever helped me to that end, to stay and be religious.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because I have a feeling that deep in me, within me, there was always a ray of hope.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't care how small it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It might have been so minuscule that you probably can't describe it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But there was in me always a minuscule belief that, one day, maybe, just maybe I'll see freedom again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I'll be able to continue in the path I once started.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Of course-- and I will be purely commentary, now, if I may add this, that the school-- this is a thought that I always also tell my children.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I tried to imbue them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "What Hitler did to me, of course, I don't wish it on anybody.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I don't wish it on myself, either.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
